&lt;p&gt;As a Software Engineer II at SeekWell, you will work with a team of developers building applications that power our business. These include primarily backend services (REST and SOAP) as well as internal applications used across the organization. You&#39;ll collaborate with engineers, QA, and Product Management to design solutions, write quality code, build automated tests, and deliver value to production. Working within our Kanban workflow in Jira, you&#39;ll have the opportunity to grow your technical skills while contributing to systems that have a direct impact on the business&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Environment&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid: Work from home with 1-2 days per week onsite in Draper, UT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occasional on-call rotation to support our 24/7 production systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain platform services and internal applications using C#, SQL, AWS, and Angular&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain code that seamlessly integrates with third-party services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build comprehensive automated tests to ensure quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate actively in collaborative code reviews and pull requests&lt;/li&gt;
